<h1>Notation Presets</h1>
<p>
  A <em>notation preset</em> controls how chord symbols are rendered — accidentals,
  quality suffixes, and special glyphs.
</p>

<h2>Built-in presets</h2>
<p>
  The following presets are available without any registration:
</p>
<ul>
  <li><strong>default</strong> — Unicode glyphs (♭ ♯ ø ° △)</li>
  <li><strong>realbook</strong> — Real Book dialect (<small>MI</small> <small>MA</small><sup>7</sup> <small>DIM</small>. etc.)</li>
</ul>

<div style="display:grid; grid-template-columns:1fr 1fr 1fr; gap:2rem; align-items:start">
  <div>
    <h3>Default preset</h3>
    <p>Unicode glyphs: ♭ ♯ ø ° △</p>
  </div>
  <div>
    <h3>&ldquo;realbook&rdquo; preset</h3>
    <p>Real Book dialect: <small>MI</small> <small>MA</small><sup>7</sup> <small>DIM</small>.</p>
  </div>
  <div>
    <h3>Custom &ldquo;ascii&rdquo; preset</h3>
    <p>ASCII alternatives: b # m7b5 dim maj7</p>
  </div>
